"All√©gories bool√©ennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

metadata.name: soft spot #45
metadata.description:
soft spot is my first published generative token.
It's the result of my curiosity in exploring dots, light and blending modes.
It features 3 possible backgrounds and 5 different palettes
and takes around 20-30s to draw so please be patient.

"S" will save a PNG from canvas using current resolution
-----------------------------------------------------
Many thanks to the inspiring notochord.xyz programming courses,
and also @nudoru, whose write up on generative brushes was a great
source on figuring out the material in which I want to draw();

written in js.

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #728
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft

metadata.name: Paradise Birds Generative Series #29
metadata.description: The Paradise Birds Generative Series is an abstracted representation of the flight of a bird and the aesthetic of the "paradise birds plant". The flight of the birds is randomly generated based on the hash provided. The system has 20 different color schemes, a varying number of birds and triangle sizes per artwork.

metadata.name: .L‚óø‚ó∏ps #2
metadata.description:
"Loop" is a fundamental property of a program that means to repeat a particular part of the program. In shape, it is the curved shape made when something long and thin, such as a piece of string, bends until one part of it nearly touches or crosses another part of it. By adding randomness to loop of repetition, I expressed it as an assembly of topological loops.


- 41*2 Color Palette
- 4 Shape Types
- 5 bands


Generative art by @ConatusLab
Built in Javascript with p5.js.


Press 's(S)' to save a png.
Press 'f(F)' to full screen.
Press '1-4' to change the resolution. The size of the dots in the background changes to give a different impression.('5-8' are similar functions, but they are experimental introductions, so the load is heavy)

metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #244
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‚ÄòOrganic Matr‚Äô (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


‚Äî‚Äî 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter‚Äôs wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‚Äòscale‚Äô parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.
